                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-07T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 7, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 7—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>408. Bay’s telegram of December 6, 11 a.m., and 4th paragraph of my telegram No.
                    407, December 6, 7 p.m.<note n="14" xml:id="d383fn14">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_561">p. 561</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Unless otherwise instructed Chapman will not depart for the United States
                    December 8, 10 p.m. as contemplated but will proceed with further endeavors to
                    obtain permission to return to Bilbao.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
